Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
report_message(25.10)                                    report_message(25.10)

Name
       report_message  -  Reports the messages that have been issued since the
       tool was launched

Syntax
       report_message

       [-help]

       [[{-errors | -warnings | -all } [-count ]] |  -suppressed  ]  [[-prefix
       <prefix> [-detail ] [-summary ]] ]

       [-detail | -count | -suppressed ] [-summary | -count | -suppressed ]

       Reports the messages that have been issued since the tool was launched.
       When  you  run report_message without any argument, it prints a summary
       table and returns no Tcl value. However, when you provide an  argument,
       it returns a list a of message IDs and does not print a table.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each  report_message  parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man report_message

       -all   Returns  a  list  of all issued message IDs as a Tcl result. The
              result does not include suppressed message IDs.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -count Returns the count of every message when -errors,  -warnings,  or
              -all is specified.

              For example, if an error appeared 20 times, command will return:

              {<Error ID> 20}

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -detail
              Returns a list of detail message of the specified prefix.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -errors
              Returns a list of issued error message IDs as a Tcl result.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -prefix <prefix>
              Returns  a list of issued error message IDs matched with -prefix
              specified as a Tcl result.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -summary
              Returns the summary of the message that has the  specified  pre-
              fix.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -suppressed
              Returns a list of suppressed message IDs as a Tcl result.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -warnings
              Returns a list of issued warning message IDs as a Tcl result.

              Data_type: bool, optional

Examples
              *

                The  following  command  prints a summary table and returns no
                Tcl value.

                report_message

